To be used for running any external application or script as a luigi Task. The code is basically a generalization of that in `luigi.contrib.spark`, and we've found it pretty useful. Is this something you would want to include in luigi? Feedback appreciated!

A trivial (and useless) example:

    class MvTask(luigi.contrib.external_program.ExternalProgramTask):
        def program_args(self):
            return ['mv', self.input().path, self.output().path]

        def input(self):
            return luigi.LocalTarget('source')

        def output(self):
            return luigi.LocalTarget('target')

If this is a reasonable idea, other task types could be "rebased" on top of this one. I've done it for `SparkSubmitTask`, and I can push that separately.

Also add an `ExternalPythonProgramTask` that allows optionally setting a virtualenv and `PYTHONPATH`.

(It's called "external _program_" (vs. "app" or "process" or "shell script"...) simply because the docs for [`subprocess.Popen`][1] refer to it as a "[child] program")

[1]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/subprocess.html#subprocess.Popen

